  "texts": [
    "This is a typical strong thermodynamic non-equilibrium effect.",
    "According to the Chapman-Enskog multi- scale analysis, when the Knudsen number is small, only the first order term in Knudsen number is significant.",
    "In other words, when the degree of TNE is low, the linear response theory works.",
    "In this case, the heat flux is positively proportional to the negative temperature gradient.",
    "But with increasing the Knudsen number, the second and even higher order terms in the Knudsen number can no longer be ignored."
  ],
